PROSOME (
Fig. 11A, C
). Consisting of cephalothorax, with fused first pedigerous somite, and second to fourth free pedigerous somites; prosomites without expansions nor spinular ornamentation; posterior hyaline frill of cephalothorax, second and third pedigerous somites broad, of P4-bearing somite visibly narrower, with posterior margins plain; posterior frill of second and third pedigerous somites with transverse row of minute spinules.

